    value: 'Baidao (伯道) was the courtesy name of Deng You of the Jin Dynasty. When fleeing the chaos of Stone Zhao, Deng You could not save both his son and nephew. He chose to sacrifice his own child to save his brother''s offspring. Later, having no heir of his own, people lamented: ''Even Heaven is pitiless, that Deng Baidao should have no son!'' The poet employs this allusion to express the paradox of the Minister''s life—a man of such virtue and service left without descendants.'
